    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-03-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-04-03T15:45:18Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation to issue regulations that require operators of cruise vessels or cruise lines to reimburse individuals for the ticket price of a cruise purchased on or before February 1, 2020, in the event of a cancellation due to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019).</p> <p>The bill applies for the duration of any emergency declared with respect to COVID-19.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To require the Secretary of Transportation to require operators of cruise vessels or cruise lines to reimburse passengers for cancellation due to COVID-19, and for other purposes.</title>
